Please read the Disclaimer, Terms and Conditions, Privacy Policy and Copyrights Notice available on the Website www.nuvamawealth.com or any agreement entered with the respective service providers for further details. 

Links given here are only guides to the various Products and the contents are property and copyright of the respective site-owner(s). The owner of these Products will take no responsibility if any damage is done by using these Products. User should note that various versions of this mobile web page are available: basic HTML and Wireless Application Protocol (WAP). To view these mobile pages, you will need a cell phone or PDA equipped with a data plan from your wireless service provider. The basic HTML pages can be viewed in a regular web browser. Please note that your wireless service provider may charge you for subscribing any data plan. 

Mobile WAP formatted web pages provided by the Products in no way constitute an endorsement of any particular service provider nor of any particular vendor of PDA devices or similar equipment which may be used to access these services. Your reception is subject to your wireless provider's area of coverage. The color and quality of images and graphics will vary with make and model of the wireless device. Depending on the capability of your device, not all available links will work. The user shall be responsible for keeping the username and password confidential and secure and shall be solely responsible for all orders entered and transactions done by any person whosoever through this Product using the Client's Username and/or password. The user shall be responsible for remembering of Password, login id and two-factor Authentication. The Password and Login id will remain same for all applications i.e. Internet Based Trading (IBT) and Securities Trading through Wireless Technology (STWT). The user aware that the changing of password at IBT application will also have the changed password for STWT application and vice-versa. The user shall immediately inform the Stock Broker of any unauthorized use of the user's Username or Password with full details or such unauthorized use including the date of such unauthorized use, the manner in which it was unauthorized used, the transactions affected pursuant to such unauthorized use etc..The User is aware that authentication technologies and strict security measures are required for the securities trading through wireless technology through order routed system and undertakes to ensure that the password of the User are not revealed to any third party including employees and dealers of the stock broker. 

The user acknowledges that he is fully aware of and understands the risks associated with availing of a service for routing orders through the mobile phone including the risk of misuse and unauthorized use of his Username and/or Password by a third party and the risk of a person hacking into the user's account on the Stock Broker's Products and unauthorized routing orders on behalf of the user through the System. The user shall be fully liable and responsible for any and all unauthorized use and misuse of his Password and/or Username and also for any and all acts done by any person through Stock Broker's Product on the user's Username in any manner whatsoever. 

The user undertakes to ensure that the password of the user and/or his authorized representative are not revealed to any third party since authentication technologies and strict security measures are required for the mobile trading though order routed system. 

The user shall log off from the product at any time when the user is not accessing or using this service and any liability incurred to the user as a consequence of the user not logging off the service shall borne solely by the user. In case of no activity by the user, the trading session will automatically log-off 

The stock broker shall send the order/trade confirmation through email to the client at his request. The client is aware that the order/ trade confirmation is also provided on the web portal. In case client is trading using wireless technology, the Stock Broker shall send the order/trade confirmation on the device of the client. 

The client is aware that trading through wireless technology will enable client to use and view only minimal features for trading and entire other features are available on the website such as Research reports, Strategies, Contract Notes, Daily Margin Statement and other reports. The gist of the risk policy is available on the website. The risk mechanism of the Stock broker will be applicable to the STWT trades in the same manner as applicable to IBT trades. 

The client is aware that STWT application is available only for NSE - Cash, F & O and Currency derivatives segment and BSE - Cash segment. For trading in other segments like MFSS, Star MF, etc the client is aware that online IBT facility is available. The client is aware that in this application there is a freeze / limit set for certain factors of trading i.e. Quantity, Price, Value and Volume. The client is aware in case of error made at the time of punching of trade, the loss will not be borne by the stock broker and client is accountable for the same. The client is aware that the limits are provided to him/her as per the risk measures of the Stock Broker. The client is required to know the current market price before mentioning the same in this application for trading. The client is aware that the all respective/related charges for usage of this application will be borne by the client including connectivity charges. 

The client is aware that in case of travelling by the client then he/she has to comply with the locals Laws of Land. This application usage for STWT by the client is subject to ensuring compliances of laws of land of that place. 

The client is aware that the data / information available on this application may change or appearing slow for trading and the real time data fields are appearing as delayed fields due to technical / connectivity problem / service provider connectivity / networking facility 

The client will have to download the version/software on his device required for trading through STWT. The client will also be required to download the upgraded version/software, whenever the same is appearing on his device before using the application. 

The client is aware that trading over the internet involves many uncertain factors and complex hardware, software, systems, communication lines, peripherals, etc. are susceptible to interruptions and dislocations. The Stock broker and the Exchange/s do not make any representation or warranty that the Stock broker's Securities trading through wireless technology Service will be available to the Client at all times without any interruption. 

The client is aware that at the time of placing of order through STWT, the order may not get executed due to various reasons such as receiving and attending calls or use of the another application in the mobile or non functioning of mobile / technical application and the client does not have any claim against the Exchange/s or the Stock broker for the same. 

The client is required to take the adequate action in case of theft, misplacement of the phone and the client does not have any claim against the Exchange/s or the Stock broker for any trades executed / loss incurred due to the trades executed after loss of the phone through STWT application. 

The client is aware that as per the regulatory requirement or as per the government or semi government order or Exchange requirement, stock broker can share the logs of the trades executed by client. Stockbroker will capture the IP for all STWT orders. The Client shall not have any claim against the Exchange or the Stock broker on account of any suspension, interruption, non-availability or malfunctioning of the Stock broker's STWT System or Service or the Exchange's service or systems or network failure / battery down or non-execution of his orders due to any link/system failure at the Client/Stock brokers/Exchange end for any reason beyond the control of the stock broker/Exchanges. 

Without prejudice to the above, the user shall immediately notify the Stock Broker in writing with full details if: 1.He discovers or suspects unauthorised access through his User name, Password or account. 2.He notices discrepancies that might be attributable to unauthorised access. 3.He forgets his password or 4.He discovers a security flaw in the product. 

In any of the above events, the user shall immediately change his Password. However, if the user is unable to change his Password by reason of his having forgotten his Password or his Password having been unauthorized changed by some other person or for any other reason then the Client shall immediately request the Stock Broker in writing to discontinue his password. At no point in time shall the Stock Broker be liable for any loss, whether notional or actual, that may be suffered by the User on account of the misuse of the Password. 

Stock broker reserves the right to make modifications and alterations to the content of the application. Users are advised to use the data for the purpose of information only and rely on their own judgment while making investment decisions. The investments recommended may not be suitable for all investors. Stock broker do not warranty the timeliness, accuracy or quality of the electronic content. 

The content of the application cannot be copied, reproduced, republished, uploaded, posted, transmitted or distributed for any non-personal use without obtaining prior permission from NWIL and/or Stock Broker, NWIL and/or Stock Broker reserves the right to terminate the accounts of subscribers/customers, who violate the proprietary rights, in addition to necessary legal action. NWIL and its owners/affiliates are not liable for damages caused by any performance, failure of performance, error, omission, interruption, deletion, defect, delay in transmission or operations, virus, phishing, hacking, communications line failure, and unauthorized access to the devices usage. NWIL is not responsible for any technical failure or malfunctioning of the software or delays of any kind. Users shall bear all responsibility of keeping the password secure. NWIL is not responsible for the loss or misuse of the password. 

Stock Broker does not warrant that your access to the site and/or related services will be uninterrupted or error-free, that defects will be corrected, or that this application or the server that makes it available is free of viruses or other harmful components. Access to and use of this application and the information is at your risk and NWIL does not undertake any accountability for any irregularities, viruses or damage that results from accessing, availing or downloading of any information from this application. 

In no event will Stock Broker be liable for any damages, including without limitation direct or indirect, major event, incidental, or consequential damages, losses or expenses arising in connection with this application or use thereof or inability to use by any party, or in connection with any failure of performance, error, omission, interruption, defect, delay in operation or transmission, computer virus or line, hanging of device or system failure. 

Corporate Office address is Eight Floor 801 to 804, Inspire BKC G Block, BKC Main Road, Bandra Kurla Complex, Bandra East, Mumbai-400051.

Nuvama Wealth and Investment Limited (NWIL) is associated with Pickright in the capacity of a distributor of Research Recommendation. All disputes with respect to the distribution activity, would not have access to Exchange investor redressal forum or Arbitration mechanism.
